        "client_msg_id": "545635fd-434b-4160-a107-baae71e1468e",
        "text": "two quotes I read today:\n\n> The unfortunate reality is that Mozilla today exists as a convenient way for monopolists to shield their companies from legal scrutiny and unpleasant discussions.\n> What I would like to say is that free software is a strategy. As a community of people that share some kind of liberatory principles of which free software has been a part, let use free software as best we can, among many other strategies. If it fits, great. If you find yourself on the same side of an argument as Palantir, it’s time to back up and try something else.\nNo manifesto survives contact with reality I guess",
        "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
        "user_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
        "source_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
        "user_profile": {
            "avatar_hash": "7f0f1c0238ec",
            "image_72": "https:\/\/avatars.slack-edge.com\/2018-07-09\/395086754178_7f0f1c0238ec02befdab_72.jpg",
            "first_name": "Mariano",
            "real_name": "Mariano Guerra",
            "display_name": "",
            "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
            "name": "mariano",
            "is_restricted": false,
            "is_ultra_restricted": false
        },
        "thread_ts": "1765982511.722009",
        "parent_user_id": "UC2A2ARPT",
        "blocks": [
            {
                "type": "rich_text",
                "block_id": "GdH9r",
                "elements": [
                    {
                        "type": "rich_text_section",
                        "elements": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "two quotes I read today:\n\n"
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "rich_text_quote",
                        "elements": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "The unfortunate reality is that Mozilla today exists as a convenient way for monopolists to shield their companies from legal scrutiny and unpleasant discussions."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "rich_text_section",
                        "elements": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "\n"
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "rich_text_quote",
                        "elements": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "What I would like to say is that free software is a strategy. As a community of people that share some kind of liberatory principles of which free software has been a part, let use free software as best we can, among many other strategies. If it fits, great. If you find yourself on the same side of an argument as Palantir, it’s time to back up and try something else."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "rich_text_section",
                        "elements": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "\nNo manifesto survives contact with reality I guess"
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
    },
